OL,3,CRiders from around the world take on
OL,4,CPenny Farthing Hill Climb in Eastbourne
OL,6,FPenny Farthings were popular during
OL,7,Fthe Victorian era and played an
OL,8,Fimportant role in launching cycling as
OL,9,Fa sport.
OL,11,FMany of the machines used in the time
OL,12,Ftrial today were modern versions of
OL,13,Fthe bike, made in Sussex. However some
OL,14,Friders did take on the climb riding
OL,15,Foriginal Victorian Penny Farthings.
OL,17,FWatch: Robert ON Torto was one of the
OL,18,Friders out today.
