OL,3,CRiders from around the world take on
OL,4,CPenny Farthing Hill Climb in Eastbourne
OL,6,FRobert ON Torto has been riding his
OL,7,FPenny Farthing for around a year and a
OL,8,Fhalf but nearly missed the event after
OL,9,Fhis bicycle was stolen and sold.
OL,11,FThanks to some detective work Robert
OL,12,Fmanaged to get it back just in time to
OL,13,Ftake part.
OL,15,FRyan Hill, who is a former BMX athlete
OL,16,Fwas given his Penny Farthing by his
OL,17,Fwife for his 30th birthday.
OL,19,FHe's been riding it now for 10 years
OL,20,Fand enjoys the peace and quiet he gets
OL,21,Fwhen riding it.
